  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. Factor the denominator of the second term: <i>a</i>&sup2;<i>b</i> &minus; 5<i>ab</i> = <i>ab</i>(<i>a</i> &minus; 5). The second term becomes <i>b</i>(<i>a</i> &minus; 5)/[<i>ab</i>(<i>a</i> &minus; 5)] = 1/<i>a</i>. Adding (<i>b</i> + 7)/(<i>a</i> &minus; 5) + 1/<i>a</i> with the common denominator <i>a</i>(<i>a</i> &minus; 5) gives [<i>a</i>(<i>b</i> + 7) + (<i>a</i> &minus; 5)] / [<i>a</i>(<i>a</i> &minus; 5)] = (<i>ab</i> + 8<i>a</i> &minus; 5)/(<i>a</i>&sup2; &minus; 5<i>a</i>). Multiplying numerator and denominator by <i>b</i> gives (<i>ab</i>&sup2; + 8<i>ab</i> &minus; 5<i>b</i>)/(<i>a</i>&sup2;<i>b</i> &minus; 5<i>ab</i>).</p><p>Choice A pairs the correct combined form with an incorrect (over-factored) denominator. Choice B fails to find a true common denominator. Choice D pairs the correct numerator with an incorrect denominator that includes an extra factor of (<i>a</i> &minus; 5).</p>",
